<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Fulham have held further talks with Benfica over a deal for Florentino Luis. </p>

<p>The Cottagers are offering around £2m for a loan fee with the option to buy the midfielder for £25m. </p>

<p>They remain in discussion with Southampton for Mario Lemina and Harrison Reed also.</p>

<p>Fulham have held further talks with Benfica over a deal for midfielder Florentino Luis</p>

<p>The Premier League new boys have activated their £8m option to sign anchorman Reed from the south coast club following their promotion to the top flight.</p>

<p>And Lemina is set to move to Craven Cottage on loan for an initial £2m fee, with an obligation for Fulham to buy him if they stay up.</p>

<p>Midfielder Reed has spent the season on loan at play-off final winners Fulham from Southampton.</p>

<p>Fulham, who beat neighbours Brentford in extra time at Wembley to secure promotion, had an option in the deal to buy Reed for £8m if they clinched promotion and a lower fee if they failed to go up.</p>

